item.title: Israel, Hezbollah traded messages following clash saying neither wants further escalation
item.description: Israel and Hezbollah engaged in a major exchange of fire, but both sides sought to avoid further escalation. Hezbollah launched rockets and drones, prompting Israel to respond with airstrikes. Israeli officials stated the strikes aimed to prevent a larger attack, while Hezbollah signaled no immediate plans for further retaliation after their initial response.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Sleepy Joe, Kamala busy campaigning': Trump warns of World War III as he slams Biden’s Middle East strategy
item.description: Reacting to the Middle East conflict, former President Donald Trump criticized President Joe Biden's administration, alleging Biden is disengaged. Trump highlighted the escalating tensions between Israel and Hezbollah, questioning US diplomacy and blaming Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris for mishandling the situation. The region faces severe tensions with military actions ongoing.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: JD Vance defends 'childless cat lady' remark: 'I’m a real person. I’m going to make jokes'
item.description: Republican VP candidate JD Vance defended his "childless cat lady" remark from a 2022 Fox News interview, asserting his comments were misinterpreted. He expressed regret for negative reactions but maintained they were meant as a joke to highlight economic and family issues. Vance reiterated his commitment to addressing high living costs and anti-family trends in the US.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'No arrest for Zuck as ...': Elon Musk attacks Meta founder amid Telegram founder Pavel Durov's arrest
item.description: Elon Musk accused Mark Zuckerberg of not adequately addressing child exploitation issues on Instagram and criticized Meta's response during a Senate hearing. Musk expressed support for Telegram's founder, Pavel Durov, who faces prison in France over similar content moderation issues. Musk also warned about declining free speech in Europe and promoted X as a platform to counter censorship.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 102 and flying high: Manette Baillie becomes Britain's oldest skydiver proving 'age is just a number'
item.description: Manette Baillie, celebrating her 102nd birthday, set a new record as Britain's oldest skydiver by jumping from a plane at 6,900 feet. Previously, at 100, she drove a Ferrari on a racing circuit. Baillie's skydive also served to raise funds for charity, and she received support from the Prince of Wales.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'I hope whoever is elected ...': Connecticut mom moves to hotel room due to high rent prices
item.description: Suzanne Hayes, a single mother in Connecticut, faced eviction after her rented home of six years was sold. Struggling with high rents and a poor credit score, she finally found relief in a $2,200 a month apartment at a local hotel. Connecticut's housing crisis remains a pressing issue for many renters.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: From 'never Trump' to running mate: Catchy remix of JD Vance's political U-turn becomes TikTok sensation
item.description: JD Vance's shift from a 'never Trump guy' in 2016 to Donald Trump's running mate in the upcoming election has sparked widespread attention. A viral TikTok remix features his old quote set to Petey Pablo's 'Freek-a-Leek' beat, amassing over 40 million views. Notably, even Vice President Kamala Harris's campaign account interacted with the viral trend, highlighting its influence.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Told PM Modi Ukraine would support India hosting 2nd summit on peace: Zelenskyy
item.description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy showed support for Prime Minister Narendra Modi's efforts to organize a second peace summit. However, Zelenskyy mentioned the summit couldn't be hosted by a non-signatory of the previous event. Discussions are ongoing with Saudi Arabia, Qatar, Turkey, and Switzerland for hosting. Modi recently visited Ukraine and affirmed India's commitment to peace.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: What is Hezbollah, the Lebanese group trading fire with Israel?
item.description: Hezbollah, an Iran-backed group, has been exchanging fire with Israel since Oct. 7, following the Gaza conflict's outbreak. Formed in 1982 by Iran’s Revolutionary Guards, Hezbollah retains significant military power. It supports Palestinian groups and has a major political role in Lebanon. Western and Sunni Arab nations label it a terrorist organization.

item.title: Hawaii braces for Hurricane Hone as storm intensifies to Category 1
item.description: Hurricane Hone, now a Category 1 storm, approached Hawaii, bringing strong winds and rain. Located south of Hilo and southeast of Honolulu, Hone raised wildfire risks in drought-affected areas. Power companies monitored situations to prevent fires from downed lines. Some beach parks closed, and shelters were prepared as the storm progressed westward.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Bangladesh metro back on track after protest closure
item.description: Bangladesh's metro railway in Dhaka resumed after over a month of closure due to student-led protests that ousted Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina. The new caretaker government under Muhammad Yunus ordered the reopening. Hasina's tenure saw widespread abuses, but the metro, inaugurated in 2022, was one of her key infrastructure projects.

item.title: Yemen Huthis hail Hezbollah strikes, renew threat to attack Israel
item.description: Yemen's Huthi rebels praised Hezbollah's attacks on Israel and threatened their own retaliation after Israeli strikes on Hodeida. The Huthis, aligned with Iran, vowed to respond to the July 20 strikes that heavily damaged the port and killed nine people. They emphasized their solidarity within Iran's 'axis of resistance.'

item.title: Kamala Harris' media silence: Is ignoring the press more damaging than Trump's attacks?
item.description: Bill Maher raised concerns about Vice President Kamala Harris' lack of media engagement compared to Donald Trump’s antagonistic approach. Maher suggested that her silence signals that the press is irrelevant. Harris has not held major press conferences since her nomination, prompting criticism for her lack of transparency and willingness to engage with the public and press.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: US reaffirms support for Rohingya on 7th anniversary of Burma genocide
item.description: US secretary of state Antony Blinken addressed the ongoing crisis in Burma, highlighting the plight of the Rohingya, and marking the seventh anniversary of their genocide. Blinken emphasized the US's commitment to humanitarian assistance, with nearly $2.4 billion contributed over seven years, and supporting the Rohingya in seeking justice and accountability for the atrocities committed against them.

item.title: Winter in August? Unseasonal snow and rain surprise west coast, disrupt travel and festivals
item.description: A rare cold weather system from the Gulf of Alaska brought unexpected snow to California and the Pacific Northwest in August. Highways were closed, and unusual snowfall was reported in places like Lassen Volcanic National Park, Minaret Vista, and Tioga Pass, disrupting travel and affecting events like the Burning Man festival in Nevada.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Hailey Welch seeks to move beyond viral fame as 'Hawk Tuah girl': 'I'd rather just be known as ...'
item.description: Hailey Welch, known for her viral "Hawk Tuah Girl" persona on TikTok, expressed her desire to be recognized beyond the nickname on the debut episode of West Wilson's dating show. She shared her aspirations to venture into podcasting and reality TV, aiming to redefine her public image.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Meghan Markle to return to UK with Prince Harry? What is her condition?
item.description: Meghan Markle has reportedly set a condition for her return to England with Prince Harry, demanding a secure and separate place to live. Their request follows their eviction from Frogmore Cottage. The couple's focus on security and residency remains key, as Prince Harry recently appealed a High Court decision on their UK security arrangements.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Matthew Perry's death: What 'Friends' actor's demise exposes about the life of celebrity assistants
item.description: Matthew Perry's tragic death on October 28, 2023, has highlighted the pressures faced by celebrity assistants. Perry's assistant, Kenny Iwamasa, confessed to injecting him with a fatal dose of ketamine. His arrest underscores the dangerous demands placed on assistants, who often face ethical dilemmas. This case reveals the challenging reality behind seemingly glamorous roles.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk
